  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/dr-cou1-noncannulated-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw, ASTM F1717 compression-bending) is accepted at the Medium assurance level. All three pre-specified QoIs meet acceptance criteria: stiffness (3.2%, E/uval=0.81), yield force (5.7%, E/uval=1.14), and force at 40 mm (7.8%, E/uval=1.52) — all within the <10% and E/uval<1.96 bounds. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, Gradation 1 vs. required Gradation 2) is accepted because ASTM F1717 mandates the single test rate, quasi-static rate insensitivity of Ti-6Al-4V is well-established in the literature, and the overall credibility profile is robust. The ContextOfUse declares an explicit bounded operating envelope (OD 7.0–8.0 mm, pitch 2.75–3.25 mm, span 45–55 mm, load 0–2500 N) with honest documentation of sparse boundary coverage. Applicability constraints explicitly prohibit extrapolation to cannulated designs, out-of-range geometries, or dynamic loading. The provenance chain is complete: validation results are traceable to bench test datasets from two ISO 17025-accredited laboratories, FEA predictions from a version-controlled ensemble, and material properties from lot-specific coupon testing. Uncertainty quantification is documented for all three QoIs. The model is fit for the stated COU within the declared operating envelope.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
